In the Rapid board quick filters tab, when user tries to create a 'Quick Filter' with invalid JQL, GUI do not provides correct error response.

Example of bad JQL (version is nonexisting field): {{version = '5.0.0.Alpha1'}}

When I try to create filter with this bad JQL (I click Add button), the ajax spinner spins forever. Error response received from the server is not reflected on GUI, no any error message is shown, which confuses users (see https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ORG-1633).

Response from the server is:
{code}
POST https://issues.jboss.org/rest/greenhopper/1.0/quickfilters/331/ 400 (Bad Request) 
{code}

Thanks for patch for this GUI issue.

*Feature Request:*
{quote}
I would like to see an additional column of subtask priority inside an Epic on the subtask list. I cannot find a way to do this. Is there a way Atlassian? or someone else know? Currently a laborious method is to open each subtask and look for the priority.
{quote}
Quote from: https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/160422/show-subtask-priority-in-an-epic

*Current Workaround:*
{quote}
I suppose an alternate way is to look at all my issues, filter by sub task, sort by propority and eyeball for the main Epic number and then hit it that way.
{quote}

