This bug was found by a customer, see this [support ticket | https://support.atlassian.com/browse/JST-61479]


Summary:
# I navigate to a rapidboard
# I transition an issue of project "A" to "Won't fix". This works and I see that the following REST endpoint is called
{noformat}
 https://clone-zimride.atlassian.net/secure/CommentAssignIssue!default.jspa?_=1366048720600&action=5&inline=true&decorator=dialog&id=19580
{noformat}
# Then I select an issue of project "B" (a different project than the issue before), and hit 'a' to assign a new user
# When I start typing usernames, I get this error (in a JS popup):
{noformat}
The JIRA server was contacted but has returned an error response. We are unsure of the result of this operation.
{noformat}
The request that failed is:
{noformat}
https://clone-zimride.atlassian.net/rest/api/latest/user/assignable/search?username=uu&projectKeys=LYFT&issueKey=LYFT-2415&actionDescriptorId=5&maxResults=1000&_=1366046680213
{noformat}
*Note the actionDescriptorId=5 URL param*. This causes the server call to fail, as there is no corresponding workflow transition for this id. From the server logs:
{noformat}
Caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: No workflow action with id '5' available for issue LYFT-2415
      at com.atlassian.jira.workflow.WorkflowTransitionUtilImpl.getActionDescriptor(WorkflowTransitionUtilImpl.java:144)
      at com.atlassian.jira.rest.v2.issue.UserResource.getActionDescriptorById(UserResource.java:308)
      at com.atlassian.jira.rest.v2.issue.UserResource.findAssignableUsers(UserResource.java:293)
      ... 199 more

{noformat}

It looks to me as of the JS code is reusing the actionDescriptorId from the previous ajaxCall (in 2.). If I start the sequence from step 3, then I can assign a user without an error.
(If I remove the _actionDescriptorId=5_ from the URL in step 4, it works)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
